# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DOCUMENTATION POLICY
#
# Two types of docs exist in this repo:
#
#   TYPE A — PROJECT DOCS (on GitHub, linked from README)
#     docs/pipeline/reference/       ← file structures, schemas, entry-point guides
#     docs/pipeline/ARCHITECTURE.md  ← layer map, module map
#     docs/pipeline/CONNECT.md       ← connector setup
#     docs/pipeline/*.md             ← stable architectural references
#
#   TYPE B — DEVELOPMENT DOCS (local only, gitignored)
#     docs/pipeline/development/     ← integration plans, audit reports, planning notes
#     docs/pipeline/integration/     ← legacy name, same rule
#     docs/project/                  ← lora-trainer planning notes
#
# Rule: if a file is a plan, analysis, audit, or working note
#       → it belongs in TYPE B → gitignored → stays on disk only.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Development docs — local only
docs/pipeline/integration/
docs/pipeline/development/
docs/project/
pipeline/audit/
_AUDIT_TEMP.md
.planning/

# Root-level development/planning docs
REMOTION_INTEGRATION.md
KOKORO_INTEGRATION.md
PRODUCTION_PIPELINE.md

# Tests — local only
tests/

# Pipeline planning and strategy guides
pipeline/CHANNEL_SYSTEM.md
pipeline/CONTENT_INTELLIGENCE.md

